The paper focuses on developing a robust automated organ segmentation method using computer vision and machine learning techniques. Specifically, it proposes a bottom-up approach for pancreas segmentation in abdominal CT scans using cascaded superpixels and deep image patch labeling. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms such as random forests and deep convolutional neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with medical image analysis, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
